description.9: The return of the Green Goblin! Guest-starring the Human Torch.
description.10: The First Appearance of Killgrave, the Purple Man!  Killgrave, the unbelievable Purple Man, with the power to control people's minds is on a crime spree in New York City. Can the Man Without Fear stop him?
description.11: Thor against the Master of Magnetism! At a local fair, Dr. Donald Blake is surprised by an attack from the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants. Will Dr. Blake slip into the guise of Thor without gaining public attention? And what is the motivation behind Magneto's civilian attack?
description.12: Taking Captain Sawyer's place temporarily, Captain Flint, Sgt. Fury, and the Howling Commandos go on a mission to destroy a convoy carrying V-2 parts through Normandy.
description.13: The Fantastic Four reunite to take down Namor, the Sub-Mariner! What is the furious King of Atlantis in a huff about now?
description.14: The Mole-Man emerges from his underground lair to bait the Fantastic Four into battle! Will the team be able to withstand his legion of Mole People? A very strange smack-down ensues.
description.20: The introduction of KANG THE CONQUEROR in his very first appearance!  Can you think of any one man whose power is greater than that of the Avengers?! Don't answer that, not until you meet...Kang the Conqueror! Kang is destined to rank as one of the most unique villains of all time..and wait till you learn his surprising identity!
description.21: A special double-sized issue! Double the action! Double the terror! Doctor Doom has the Fantastic Four right where he wants them. Will the FF be able to stand against their menace? Also featuring the twisted back story of Doctor Doom, the Fantastic Four's cruelest nemesis to date.
description.22: Thor is summoned by Dr. Strange while rescuing a child from a speeding truck. On his arrival to the Sanctum Santorum, Thor finds the doctor passed out on the floor! What mystical forces have incapacitated Dr. Strange? Enter Baron Mordo!
description.23: RACING AGAINST TIME! Nick Fury's squad has 72 hours to get from England to Okinawa, find Colonel Phil Parker, break him out, and get off the island - and that's when the carpet bombing begins.
description.24: Thing has his jet stolen from right beneath him! Here comes the Torch to save the day (and to save his friend's flying machine)!
description.25: The First Appearance of the Avenging Archer Hawkeye!  How can a man with nothing more than a bow and trick arrows go toe-to-toe with Iron Man? And is he a bona fide hero or a common thief? Ol Shell-Head encounters Hawkeye, the marksman!
description.30: The First Appearance of Kraven the Hunter!  After their latest tussle, the Chameleon is more determined than ever to eliminate Spider-Man as a threat! To do so, he enlists the aid of Kraven the Hunter.
description.31: The First Appearance of the Owl!  Daredevil battles The Owl, the overlord of all crime in Manhattan! Matt Murdock must defeat The Owl in order to save Karen Page!
description.32: Thor vs. the Grey Gargoyle! Following the confusion over his identity, Thor attempts to stage reconciliation between Thor and Dr. Blake for the sake of Jane. Dr. Blake becomes the sole hero in the battle with Grey Gargoyle!
description.33: MISSION: CAPTURE HITLER! Fury and the Howling Commandos are sent into Germany to capture Adolf Hitler himself.
description.34: The Torch and the Thing have a brand new enemy! Enter...the Beetle!
description.35: Captain America guest-stars! Cap calls on Giant-Man and Wasp when the rest of the Avengers are off on a mission. Why are the two heroes off to Bura-Bura? Plus, Wasp takes on the Magician...alone!
description.41: Mr. Hyde and Cobra continue to give Thor trouble, when they prevent him from switching in and out of his human form. During the battle, "Dr. Blake" is able to apprehend both villains, but must identify Thor as a vigilante god to protect his identity. Back at the office, Jane feels betrayed by Dr. Blake as she knows Thor to be a hero. How much longer can Thor live a double-life?
description.42: Nick Fury and his Commandos are ordered to capture a Nazi scientist who has created a "death ray".
description.43: One bad guy may not be enough to defeat the Torch. Maybe not even two. But three? That's when things get interesting!
description.44: The Egghead is back, and now Spider-Man's involved! But why is Spidey throwing down with Giant-Man's villain? Wasp's stings powers get an upgrade!
description.46: The First Appearance of the GREEN GOBLIN!  Complete with his flying broomstick and goblin armor, the Green Goblin tests his mettle in a faceoff with Spider-Man. Guest starring the Incredible Hulk!
description.47: The First Appearance of Masters of Evil and the First Full Appearance of the original Baron Zemo!  Cap's wartime nemesis Baron Zemo wants him dead again, and he's gathered the Avengers' individual enemies to handle the job!
description.51: A lovesick Thor confronts his feelings for Jane Foster. Under the guise of Dr. Donald Blake, Thor dreams of the life he could lead. Jane believes Dr. Blake does not love her as he remains distant. Wasp presses Thor about his love life, but Giant Man steps in to prevent an awkward conversation. In his office, Thor, as Dr. Blake, is attacked by the Cobra and Mr. Hyde!
description.52: Sometimes your dreams transform into reality. Dreams of battling the Plantman are no exception.
description.53: Giant-Man stages a "fake yacht party" to capture the latest villain on the scene....the Magician! A madman with a plan, the Magician pulls the wool over his victims' eyes, only to rob them blind! Meanwhile, Hank and Janet have difficulty expressing their true feelings for each other.
description.54: Meet our Web-Head’s newest foe: Mysterio, the Master of Illusion!
description.60: Loki berates his lackeys Enchantress and Executioner for failing to disarm Thor. On Midgard, Thor encounters Skaag, a massive Storm Giant that escaped Asgard after getting past Balder. Now, Thor and Balder must defeat Skaag and his fire demon before mortal life is lost!
description.61: Sgt. Fury and former classmate Lieutenant Parker get into a scuffle that causes German forces to drop a bomb and knock Sgt. Fury out!
description.62: The power of Fire and Ice comes together! It's the Human Torch and Iceman's first meeting!
description.63: Escape of the Human Top! David Cannon has learned a new trick, one that lets him appear invisible to the naked eye! With Cannon back on the streets, will New York ever feel safe? Giant-Man and Wasp answer the call, and their plan of attack involves lots and lots of ants!
description.65: Spider-Man confronts J. Jonah Jameson about his constant negative reporting in the Daily Bugle. Meanwhile, Doctor Octopus is in the middle of a nationwide crime spree!
description.68: Featuring the Enchantress! After Odin realizes that he cannot deter Thor's love for Jane Foster, he enlists the help of Loki to find an immortal mate for his son. Enter Amora, a beautiful sorceress so deadly, that the Asgardians fear her power! Will Thor be able to resist the advances of Loki's latest plot? And will Jane Foster stick around after witnessing the Enchantress in action?
description.69: Torch is having some girl problems, but he has several other super hero issues to combat as well!
description.70: The first appearance of Natasha Romanov, the Black Widow! The future Avenger finds herself in the middle as Iron Man and Crimson Dynamo test their mettle against each other!
description.71: Giant-Man and Wasp share tension over taking a vacation. But Wasp may get her wish sooner than she realized; Hank and Janet travel to Santo Rico to deliver the country of a communist tyrant! Who is El Toro, the madman who slid his way into presidency?
description.78: With his powers halved by an angry Odin, Thor is left defenseless and distraught. In an attempt to please Odin and regain his abilities, Thor accepts a dangerous mission from the 23rd century. Will Thor be able to save 20th century earth, by destroying Arthur Zarrko of the future?
description.79: Sgt. Fury is ordered to attack Rommel, but with Dino Manelli injured the Commandos are forced to replace him with George Stonewell, a true troublemaker!
description.80: The Wizard is in disguise! Will the Torch fall for the elaborate ruse?
description.81: The return of Porcupine! While performing for kids at a local orphanage, the Porcupine sets a trap that Giant-Man and Wasp can't ignore. Will Giant-Man be able to save Wasp when he, and the chips, are down? Plus, Janet shares a science fiction story!
description.83: Spider-Man squares off against the awesome might of the Enforcers!
description.84: The Return of Captain America as he joins the Avengers!  The legend lives! Captain America steps out of the ice and into the Modern Era, helping the Avengers against enemies alien and Atlantean!
description.87: Thor goes on a rampage through New York City after his father Odin denies him a marriage with Jane Foster. Unaware of the damage his tantrum is causing, Hank Pym as Giant Man must step in to appeal to Thor's conscience. Also featuring Iron Man!
description.88: The Eel hasn't done anything wrong...yet! The Human Torch is suspicious to say the least.
description.89: Enter the Black Knight! After Giant-Man upsets the wrong Communists, a 'hero' in the name of their regime rises. But how exactly did the Knight get a winged horse?
description.90: Meet the super-powered villain Electro! Does the Web-Slinger have the power to stop him?
description.97: Baron Von Strucker is ordered by Hitler himself to defeat Nick Fury in a duel.
description.98: The Puppet Master has a few tricks up his sleeves that even our heroes can't control. All he had to do was create a puppet of the Torch and the Thing...
description.99: Hank continues to push himself in speed trials. Will Giant-Man ever be fast enough to catch the Human Top? Janet's concern for Hank grows, while the Top's trail of chaos ends!

9.text: Flash Thompson invites everyone to attend the first meeting of the Spider-Man fan-club, except Peter Parker! Plus, the Return of the Green Goblin!

10.text: Killgrave, the unbelievable Purple Man with the power of people's minds is on a crime spree in New York City. Can the Man Without Fear stop him?

16.text: Witness the debut of the adept alchemist Diablo. Is this mysterious new superhuman friend or foe? And can he succeed in curing the Thing where Reed failed?

17.text: Having undergone a form of powerful hypnotic suggestion, Spider-Man duels with Daredevil, the Man Without Fear!

20.text: Kang the Conqueror has come! He wants the Earth, and he's got time on his side - but on Earth's side are...the Avengers!

Kang the Conqueror is introduced as "one of the most unique villains of all time!" on this classic cover by Jack Kirby and Dick Ayers.  Unique may be a bit of an understatement, though, as the time-traveling villain is shown standing up to the might of the entire Avengers line-up!
Kang the Conqueror has come! He wants the Earth, and he's got time on his side - but on Earth's side are...the Avengers!

26.text: The Blob joins the Brotherhood! He's fighting mad at the X-Men, but can he and Magneto even count on each other?

27.text: Tony Stark is off gallivanting like the billionaire playboy he is and Iron Man nowhere to be found -- so who will save the Avengers from the threat of the uncanny Unicorn?

28.text: The Fantastic Four enter into a rematch against the Red Ghost and his Super-Apes! Guest-starring the Watcher!

29.text: The Masters of Evil go godly when the Enchantress and the Executioner join their ranks! Magic means mayhem when Thor is turned against his fellow Avengers!
The Masters of Evil go godly when the Enchantress and the Executioner join their ranks! Magic means mayhem when Thor is turned against his fellow Avengers!

30.text: Spider-Man becomes the most dangerous game in a battle of cat and mouse with Kraven the Hunter!

31.text: Daredevil battles The Owl, the overlord of all crime in Manhattan! Matt Murdock must defeat The Owl in order to save Karen Page!

39.text: Will Tony Stark be able to free himself from the clutches of his most malevolent foe â€" or can no one, not even Iron Man, escape the Mandarin? Plus: insight on the new MK III armor!

40.text: The X-Men guest-star as they and the Fantastic Four face the combined menace of the Puppet Master, Mad Thinker, and the Awesome Android!

45.text: The X-Men and Brotherhood are evenly matched, and both teams think Namor the Sub-Mariner can turn the tide in their favor! Too bad no one told them that in the war between good and evil, Namor's just as likely to fight both sides!

46.text: The first major battle between Spidey and his archnemesis, the Green Goblin!

47.text: Cap's wartime nemesis Baron Zemo wants him dead again, and he's gathered the Avengers' individual enemies to handle the job! First appearance of the Masters of Evil!
Cap's wartime nemesis Baron Zemo wants him dead again, and he's gathered the Avengers' individual enemies to handle the job! First appearance of the Masters of Evil!

48.text: Even with a new set of Iron Man armor at his disposal, will Tony Stark finally be bested by his greatest nemesis, the Mandarin?

49.text: The Invisible Girl is kidnapped by Namor the Sub-Mariner, Prince of Atlantis! The remaining members of the Fantastic Four enlist the aid of Doctor Strange to expedite their rescues efforts!

50.text: Daredevil vs. Electro! What chance does a blind man have against the master of electricity? Plus, an appearance by the Fantastic Four's The Thing!

54.text: Rumor has it that Spider-Man has been become a thief, robbing establishments in the middle of the night. Little does the public know that someone else is behind all these robberies...and his name is Mysterio!

57.text: The Lava Men have a burning desire to conquer the world, and it's up to the Avengers to stop them! Guest-starring the Hulk!
The Lava Men have a burning desire to conquer the world, and it's up to the Avengers to stop them! Guest-starring the Hulk!

58.text: Despite an earlier defeat, the Black Widow's prospects are looking up - thanks to an anti-gravity ray that can send buildings into the air! Can Iron Man get her to keep it down a little?
Despite an earlier defeat, the Black Widow's prospects are looking up - thanks to an anti-gravity ray that can send buildings into the air! Can Iron Man get her to keep it down a little?

59.text: The Hulk continues his rampage through New York City, but the Avengers have arrived to challenge their former member. Can the FF and Earth's Mightiest Heroes work together to stop the Jade Giant?

64.text: Abducted to Asteroid M! Magneto's got an X-Man in his clutches and a team of underlings waiting for the rescue party!

65.text: In a daring battle against Dr. Octopus, Spider-Man is unmasked in broad daylight!

66.text: Things heat up between Betty Brant and Peter Parker. Plus, the return of Doctor Octopus!

67.text: The battle you've been waiting for! The Incredible Hulk vs. the Ever Lovin' Blue-Eyed Thing! Nuff said!

70.text: When Natasha met Tony: the first appearance of the Black Widow! Iron Man vs. the Crimson Dynamo with Marvel's original spider woman in the middle!
When Natasha met Tony: the first appearance of the Black Widow! Iron Man vs. the Crimson Dynamo with Marvel's original spider woman in the middle!

72.text: The origin of Daredevil, The Man Without Fear!  Matt Murdock is blinded but gains super power abilities he uses to patrol Hell's Kitchen.

76.text: The Scarecrow puts some fear into Iron Man...how will Tony Stark overcome his new foe?
In his first appearance, the sinister Scarecrow tries to put the fear in Iron Man! Armor vs. rags...and crows!

77.text: A strange extra-terrestrial being is wreaking havoc on Earth! The FF must deal with a threat the likes of which they've never faced before: the Infant Terrible!

82.text: Magneto's back, and he's not alone! The X-Men and the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants battle for the first time!

83.text: Spider-Man versus The Big Man and The Enforcers!

84.text: The legend lives! Captain America steps out of the ice and into the Modern Era, helping the Avengers against enemies alien and Atlantean!
The legend lives! Captain America steps out of the ice and into the Modern Era, helping the Avengers against enemies alien and Atlantean!

85.text: In his first appearance, the sinister Scarecrow tries to put the fear in Iron Man! Armor vs. rags...and crows!
In his first appearance, the sinister Scarecrow tries to put the fear in Iron Man! Armor vs. rags...and crows!

86.text: The diabolical Dr. Doom gathers a new super-villain group, the Terrible Trio! Can the Fantastic Four defeat their greatest nemesis when he's backed by his own team?

90.text: Witness the birth of a classic Spider-Man villain, a man called Electro!

93.text: Earth's mightiest heroes must face Marvel's mightiest malcontents: the Hulk and the Sub-Mariner, teaming up for the first time! Featuring the Fantastic Four and the X-Men!
Earth's mightiest heroes must face Marvel's mightiest malcontents: the Hulk and the Sub-Mariner, teaming up for the first time! Featuring the Fantastic Four and the X-Men!

94.text: The Armored Avenger vs. a mutant gone mad! Guest-starring the X-Men!
The Armored Avenger vs. a mutant gone mad! Guest-starring the X-Men!

95.text: The Fantastic Four's first foe returns with a vengeance! The mighty Mole Man's plan is to sink the world's largest cities down to his level, and he already has a plan to deal with the FF!

96.text: Thor and Mister Hyde throw down! Plus, has Thor finally figured out a way to wed his beloved Jane Foster?
